import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='temperature', kde=True, color='blue', bins=20)
    plt.axvline(data['temperature'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['temperature'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of temperature?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temperature', data=data, legend='brief')
    plt.title('How does temperature vary with time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.legend(title='Temperature', loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
